div.ab:
83. Filled with grain, grapes, and fruits;
 
in the other hand he grasps a rudder,
 
indicating that along the courses of his waters,
 
one navigates with great Ships and Barges
 
from Rome to the Sea, 
 
over and over again; this is understood, 
 
for further explanation, from the Base, 
 
on which are made ships sailing up and down.
